cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the use of imaging techniques for the identification of plant species, specifically Brachiaria, using fractal descriptors and a state-of-the-art classifier. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper involves the analysis of images and the extraction of relevant information from them. The use of a classifier also suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the scanning of leaf samples, which could involve the use of microscopy and imaging techniques (cs.MM).
